      "actionDate": "2025-01-03",
      "actionDesc": "Introduced in House",
      "text": "<p>This concurrent resolution authorizes Congress to assemble at a place outside Washington, DC, during the 119th Congress if the Speaker of the House and the Senate Majority Leader agree that it is in the public interest.&nbsp;The concurrent resolution provides that&nbsp;the Speaker of the House and the Senate Majority Leader shall act jointly after consultation with the House and Senate Minority Leaders.</p>",
